{"title":"EF Education-EasyPost will race the Giro d’Italia on recycled paint Cannondales","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/ef-education-rapha-cannondale-giro-italia/","date":1683311426000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-collection-downtubess.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"EF Education-EasyPost will race the Giro d’Italia on recycled paint Cannondales\" /></figure>\r\n<p>At this point, it is almost expected that teams <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/tag/ef-education-first/\" target=\"_blank\">EF Education-EasyPost</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/tag/ef-education-tibco-svb/\" target=\"_blank\">EF Education-Tibco-SVB</a> drop some sort of new, exclusive, or unique kit just in time for the <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/tag/giro-ditalia/\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia</a>. Largely it was out of necessity, as EF’s team kit was a similar enough shade of pink to the maglia rosa leader’s jersey to require a change. <br /><br />Following on the heels of a collaboration kit with skateboarding brand Palace in 2020, and two more swap out kits the following years, this year’s kit is a patchwork of material that features 72 percent recycled materials in a nod to the team’s sustainability initiatives. These kits follow a new <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/tag/rapha/\" target=\"_blank\">Rapha</a> kit release called Rapha Excess, <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/raphas-new-excess-program-turns-scrap-material-into-new-kits/\" target=\"_blank\">which you can read more about here</a>.</p>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-complete.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-complete\" width=\"1500\" height=\"2250\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-complete.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-complete.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>We need more colors in the pro peloton! Good to see both EF teams expand their palette, and better to see it done with an eye toward sustainability. (Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p>Like years prior, EF has also released a small run of specially-painted race bikes for the race to accentuate the special kits. <br /><br />The custom-painted frames use the recently released Lab71 Cannondale SuperSix Evo frames. None of the frames are new, instead repainting already-produced frames for the race. Better still, each frame is hand-painted meaning no two rider bikes will be identical.</p>\r\n<p>These frames are designed to be team-only and will not be available for purchase. Sorry Cannondale fans!</p>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-collection-downtubess.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-collection-downtubess\" width=\"1333\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-collection-downtubess.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-collection-downtubess.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>No two frames will be the same as each uses recycled paint. That said, the color palette will match the new recycled Rapha kits.</figcaption></figure>\r\n<figure>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n</figure>\r\n<figure>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-headtube.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-headtube\" width=\"1600\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-headtube.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-headtube.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n</figure>\r\n<figure>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-process.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-process\" width=\"1600\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-process.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-process.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n</figure>\r\n<figure>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-riding.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-riding\" width=\"1500\" height=\"996\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-riding.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-riding.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n</figure>\r\n<figure>\r\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth-2.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth-2\" width=\"1600\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth-2.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Team-EF-Education-First-Cannondale-custom-paint-booth-2.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Tim Wilkey/Jared Gruber/Ashley Gruber)</figcaption></figure>\r\n</figure>\r\n<figure></figure>","author":"Alvin Holbrook","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"02098c64badecd9aa8950ee0365d0d0695ddfbf1213b31107b292507f03a4e24","category":"Cycling"}